(209, '48 Canvas is completely sold out - All thanks to you', '<div class="bodytext">\r\n			 <p style="float:right;"><a href="media-news.asp?nYear=2013&mon=" class="back">Back</a></p>\r\n				          <div class="mediaprtitle">48 Canvas is completely sold out - All thanks to you</div>\r\n				          <p style="font-size:12px!important;">[20&nbsp;September,&nbsp;2013]</p>\r\n				          <p><p>Supertech has crossed yet another milestone. 48 Canvas at Sector 79. the exclusive 4 BHK ''Bare Shell'' residential project has been completely sold out in just a short span of time. This momentous achievement wouldn''t have been possible but for you. It''s  you who believed in the project all through. It''s you who actually made 48 Canvas a reality. We thank you for all your trust and support. For this project exists because of you.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<table width="720" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">\r\n    <tbody>\r\n       \r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>&nbsp</td>\r\n            <td align="right">\r\n			&nbsp</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n       \r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>\r\n			<img border="0" src="http://supertechlimited.com/images/48-canvas.jpg" alt="" /></td>\r\n            <td align="right">&nbsp\r\n            </td>\r\n			</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</p>\r\n										<p>\r\n                      </p>\r\n					\r\n				          \r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n  <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n			          </div>', 0, 1, '2013-09-20 00:00:00', 0),
(210, 'A Revolutionary Future - Precast Technology', '<div class="bodytext">\r\n			 <p style="float:right;"><a href="media-news.asp?nYear=2013&mon=" class="back">Back</a></p>\r\n				          <div class="mediaprtitle">A Revolutionary Future - Precast Technology</div>\r\n				          <p style="font-size:12px!important;">[20&nbsp;September,&nbsp;2013]</p>\r\n				          <p><p>Meeting the project deadlines and giving possessions on time is a challenge and the ability to meet such challenges defines a company''s credibility in the market. This challenge of meeting and beating the deadlines can easily be met with the use to latent technologies that are the future of construction.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Supercast is Supertech''s endeavour in precast technology through which concrete is cast into a reusable mold, cured and then transported to the construction site and lifts into place as opposed to standard concrete which is poured on-site into specific forms. Supercast uses cutting-edge technology to create precast concrete precisely cast in a controlled environment and properly cured. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The first factory for Supertech Precast Technology Private Limited has been set up in Greater Noida with a production capacity of 5 million sq. ft. area per annum, and all machines and units have been imported from Germany. This technology will not only help the Group deliver projects before time but will also equip it to rise above the highly competitive market scenario.  Currently Supercast is used in various projects namely The Upcountry at Yamuna Expressway and Ecovillage at Greater Noida (West).</p></p>\r\n										<p>\r\n                      </p>\r\n					\r\n				          \r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n  <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n			          </div>', 0, 1, '2013-09-20 00:00:00', 0),
(211, 'Supertech adopts 10 villages to extend help', '<div class="bodytext">\r\n			 <p style="float:right;"><a href="media-news.asp?nYear=2013&mon=" class="back">Back</a></p>\r\n				          <div class="mediaprtitle">Supertech adopts 10 villages to extend help</div>\r\n				          <p style="font-size:12px!important;">[11&nbsp;July,&nbsp;2013]</p>\r\n				          <p><p>Dehradun, July 11, ''13: Supertech Limited, a leading real estate developer has come forward to extend help to the victims of Uttarakhand calamity caused by the devastating flood. The company will adopt ten villages of Uttarakhand and help them to come back to their normal life. The company will provide temporary electricity arrangements, and will also undertake essential repairs to the school and dispensary buildings which have been badly affected in the tragedy.   </p>\r\n\r\n <p>Mr. R.K. Arora, CMD, Supertech Limited, in the presence of Honorable Chief Minister of Uttarakhand, Mr. Vijay Bahaguna, announced about the company''s initiative in a program held at Dehradun today.</p>\r\n<p>Speaking on the occasion, Mr. R.K. Arora, CMD, Supertech Limited, said, "Being a responsible corporate citizen we have always tried to extend our helping hands to those who are badly in need. If our contribution can help the people who are suffering from this tragedy, we feel privileged in doing so".</p>\r\n\r\n <p>Supertech is helping victims of 10 affected villages in districts of Uttarkashi and Rudraprayag. It is providing food items like refined oil, lentils, flour, salt, sugar, spices, milk powder etc., essential items like medicines, soaps, blankets, temporary shelters/tents and solar battery lights etc. in the flood affected regions.</p>\r\n\r\n <p>The company will be sending 5 trucks from Dehradun containing the above items. To offer further assistance in re-settlement and monitoring the activities, Supertech will also be sending its team of 10 people versatile with local conditions to these districts.</p>\r\n\r\n<table width="720" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">\r\n    <tbody>\r\n       \r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>From LtoR -Mr. Mohit Arora, Director, Supertech Ltd , Honble Chief Minister of Uttrakhand, Mr. R.K. Arora, CMD, Supertech Ltd</td>\r\n            <td align="right">\r\n			&nbsp</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n       \r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>\r\n			<img border="0" src="http://supertechlimited.com/images/Dehradun.jpg" alt="" /></td>\r\n            <td align="right">&nbsp\r\n            </td>\r\n			</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</p>\r\n										<p>\r\n                      </p>\r\n					\r\n				          \r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n  <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n			          </div>', 0, 1, '2013-07-11 00:00:00', 0),
(212, 'Supertech Facilitates Victims of Uttarakhand Catastrophe', '<div class="bodytext">\r\n			 <p style="float:right;"><a href="media-news.asp?nYear=2013&mon=" class="back">Back</a></p>\r\n				          <div class="mediaprtitle">Supertech Facilitates Victims of Uttarakhand Catastrophe</div>\r\n				          <p style="font-size:12px!important;">[1&nbsp;July,&nbsp;2013]</p>\r\n				          <p><p>To extend help to the victims of Uttarakhand calamity, Supertech Limited is sending relief material to different parts of the state. The company is helping victims of 10 affected villages in districts of Uttarkashi and Rudraprayag. It is providing food, medicines, books, blankets, temporary shelter and electricity in the flood affected regions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Supertech had sent the relief material to these regions on June 28 and June 30. It sent 5 trucks from Dehradun on 28th which contained bags full of medicines, mineral water, blankets, refined oil, utensils, tents and a temporary electricity arrangement through generators. On 30th, it sent 3 trucks from Noida containing rice, refined oil, lentils, flour, salt, sugar, spices, milk powder, soaps, medicines and temporary tents so that people can re-locate themselves and meet their daily requirements. It is also sending cement and tar to repair the roads for easy commutation. To offer further assistance in re-settlement and monitor the activities, Supertech has also sent its team of 10 people to the districts.</p>\r\n\r\n<table width="720" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">\r\n    <tbody>\r\n       \r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>&nbsp</td>\r\n            <td align="right">\r\n			&nbsp</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n       \r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>\r\n			<img border="0" src="http://www.supertechlimited.com/images/uttrakhand2.JPG" alt="" /></td>\r\n            <td align="right">\r\n            <img border="0" src="http://www.supertechlimited.com/images/uttrakhand.JPG" alt="" /></td>\r\n			</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n </tbody>\r\n</table></p>\r\n										<p>\r\n                      </p>\r\n					\r\n				          \r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n  <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n			          </div>', 0, 1, '2013-07-01 00:00:00', 0);
